revision.text:
Colonel '''Dương Hiếu Nghĩa''' (born c. 1925, [[Sa Đéc]]) was an officer in the [[Army of the Republic of Vietnam]]. He graduated from the [[Da Lat|Đà Lạt]] National Military Academy. During the [[Vietnam War]], he served in various infantry and armored units. His highest administrative position was Province Chief of [[Vinh Long|Vĩnh Long]].
He, along with Captain [[Nguyen Van Nhung|Nguyễn Văn Nhung]], executed President [[Ngo Dinh Diem|Ngô Đình Diệm]] and the President's confidant, his brother [[Ngo Dinh Nhu|Ngô Đình Nhu]] after the latter were arrested at the end of an [[1963 South Vietnamese coup|army coup]]. After the [[Fall of Saigon]] in 1975, Nghia spent at least a dozen years in various re-education camps. In 1992, he was allowed to emigrate to the United States under the Humanitarian Orderly Departure Program. {{Citation needed|date=December 2011}}
